title: For Sale:  Type 53 Mosin Nagant
postcontent:
Hello I am selling a Chinese Type 53 Mosin Nagant that has an ATI stock on it.  

The Type 53s' were made on the same Soviet tooling that was used to make the M44 carbines, but it was sent to communist China after the USSR started transitioning into making AKs, and many of them saw action in Vietnam.  Unfortunately, the Chinese were not very good at fishing their stocks, and the one on this one was pretty rotten and had to be ditched.  

From the pictures you can see that this gun is a little rough, but hey its only 100 bucks for a piece of history with a side folding bayonet! Its a blast to shoot, 7.62x54r is cheap, and if nothing else you could bury this and not feel too bad about it. (kidding!)

If interested please text REDACTED and ask for A.J.

Cash only, and you will need to have a valid OR drivers license and be willing to fill out a bill of sale. Thanks for looking!

title: For Trade:  Stoeger Cougar 8000 (Beretta)
postcontent:
I have a beautiful Stoeger Cougar 8000
Chambered in 9mm
Comes with 3 15 round mags

Here's what their website says about it:

Stoeger 8000 Cougar Pistols: Champions of Tactical Reliability

The new Stoeger 8000 Cougar semi-auto pistols inherit the reputation of the original Beretta 8000 as reliable, durable and powerful. First designed primarily for tactical undercover work, the Cougar is now carried by a growing number of police officers as their official duty sidearm thanks to its ergonomics, low recoil and inherent accuracy. The original Beretta Cougar was NATO qualified and boasted a long service-life of more than 30,000 9mm rounds. In its new incarnation, Beretta has developed an ergonomically-advanced pistol that is compact but capable of handling high-power cartridges, offering high magazine capacity and giving a long service life. This has been possible also thanks to the innovative adaptation of a locked-breech system with a rotating barrel. Today, the new Stoeger 8000 Cougar pistol is manufactured by the Stoeger Silah Sanayi A.S., strictly in line with the most traditional Beretta quality control and attention to detail.


Low Recoil

Upon firing this pistol, shooters are amazed by the low felt recoil. This is due to two factors working together. The first is the rotating barrel system, which dissipates recoil radially rather than directing it into the shooter’s hand. The second is the central block, which absorbs the mechanical recoil from the barrel and the slide before this is transferred to the frame. When the Cougar is in battery, the positive lock-up of barrel to slide assures perfect alignment of barrel and sights. Upon firing, the barrel travels and rotates with axial movement. Besides low recoil, the result is superior accuracy and quicker recovery for follow-up shots.


Advanced Ergonomics for Easy Handling, Control, Concealment

The Cougar is one of the most ergonomically advanced pistols in its class. The user-friendly, contoured frame and grips make the Cougar exceptionally easy to control during firing. By taking hand anatomy and instinctive hold into account, the Cougar accommodates smaller hands and also protects larger hands from being bitten by the slide. All edges are rounded or beveled, and are carefully finished to make the Cougar virtually snag-proof and exceptionally easy to draw and conceal.


Different Configurations to Suit Most Tactical Needs

The Cougar L Type P is conceived to deliver high firepower in F or D (Double Action Only) operating systems. F models have the same safety features of the famous Beretta 92 FS pistol: external ambidextrous manual safety with decocking lever, trigger bar disconnect, rotating firing pin striker, firing pin block device and loaded-chamber indicator. The double-action-only D versions have the firing pin block device and the loaded-chamber indicator but no manual safety, thereby offering a super-smooth, exceptionally snag-free side. Both versions are manufactured in 9 mm or .40 caliber to satisfy the different needs of police officers and concealed-carry permit holders.
The 8000 Cougar L 9mm pistol, available in F or D configurations, features the same rotating barrel system of the full-size Cougar L Type P; the difference is in the shortened grip frame that houses a 13-round, high-capacity double-stack magazine. The beveled slide and the reduced dimensions and weight also make this model ideal for undercover work.

Visit us online www.BlackhawkTactical.org

Training Day # 1 Saturday August 9th 2014

Class Starts: 9am / Class Ends: 7:30pm



This course is designed to provide beginner and advanced shooters with the knowledge, skills and attitude necessary for safely owning and using a firearm. Phase 1 of our course is primarily marksmanship and safety based instruction to provide our students with the fundamentals needed to become an accurate marksman while applying the safety principles taught throughout this course. Our instruction staff uses state of the art technology to address a breakdown of fundamentals, make corrections and teach our students to become highly accurate marksman in our classroom and at the range. We cater to all levels of experience and our classroom setting is a 100% hands-on approach to firearms and our students go hands-on multiple times during this course to ensure safety principles and fundamentals are being executed before live firing of a pistol is introduced. 

  Upon completion of classroom portion our students are given a written examination in accordance with Illinois State Police training standards and are dismissed to the gun range immediately following the grading of the exam. Generally the classroom portion runs until 5pm but may run slightly later based upon class size and comprehension of the material. Blackhawk Tactical utilizes Rinks Gun Range in Lockport, IL please see below for the Illinois State Police CCL life fire qualifications.

Some of the Topics Covered:



Pistol Components: Semi-Automatic  Revolver Pistol Actions: Semi-Automatic  Revolver  Pistol Functions: Semi-Automatic Revolver Ammunition Components 
Personal Protection Ammo Selection Ammunition Malfunctions Tap/Rack/Assess Practical Drills One/Two Handed Grip 

Aiming:  Sight Alignment vs. Sight Picture
 Hold Control Trigger Control Breath Control 
Fundamental Follow Through  Benchrest Postion Isosceles Position Weaver Position(s)  
Range Safety Protocol Pistol Cleaning: Semi-Automatic Revolver Pistol Storage: Home and Automobile Firearm Safety Rules 

 During Phase I you will go hands on various times  to demonstrate loading/unloading of both semi-automatics and revolvers, safety fundamentals marksmanship skills prior to the live firing portion of this class. To do this you will utilize SIRT dryfiring technology in our classrooms that is used by Swat Teams, Military Branches and Law Enforcement during training drills.  The SIRT pistol is a fully weighted, semi-functional Glock 17 replica, 100% inert with laser feedback. This technology is excellent in providing instant feedback on aim (sight picture and sight alignment) , trigger control, hold control, breath control and follow through fundamentals. This advanced technology allows us to preserve a safe environment for our students while incorporating real world scenarios where practice and fundamental implementation saves lives! 



dfsf.jpg





Training Day #2  - Sunday August 10th  2014 

Class Starts 11am / Class Ends 5pm (Approx)  



Phase II of this course implements all of the fundamentals learned in the first portion of our course. Defensive shooting skills require a more refined, advanced approach and you will learn how to utilize the skills you have demonstrated and apply them to a potential lethal encounter. The skills and tactics taught in this portion of the course will ensure not only you stay safe while carrying your firearm but also ensures that those around you are safe as well.  

The course concludes with our Federal and State legal instruction. Immediately following dismissal you will have the option to be fingerprinted and have your application completed with our assistance. You walk out of our classroom 100% done and waiting on your permit. We encourage all of you to continue your training long after our course and are always welcome back to our classroom sessions at any time 100% FREE of charge. We look forward to seeing you in training!

title: For Sale/Trade:  Hornady .22 cal seating die
postcontent:
Had a ruined full length sizer (my fault), had to buy a new die. Needed to get back to reloading and shipping would take to long. Decided to just buy another die set. Now I have a second .22 cal seating die that I have no use for.

I believe it is the 3.7" seater, which would be Hornady part number 044102. Hornady's site: http://www.hornady.com/store/22-Cal-.224-Seating-Die-3.7-1-Each/ I'm not 100% on that, it could be the 4". The outside of the die measures 3.9" full length, so I'm guessing it's the 3.7"

This would be the die meant for .22 cal bullets, not cartridge specific. It will work for commons like .222rem, .223rem, 22-250 as well as some of the less common .22 cal cartridges.

If you have never used a Hornady seating die, they are amazing. They have a free floating sleeve that aligns the bullet BEFORE it reaches the seating stem. Say goodbye to crocked bullets and crushed cases!

I also love Hornady's lock rings over RCBS's, they don't use a brass screw into the threads that strips out. They squeeze tight around the threads with a steel ring and screw.

This would be great for someone who plans on loading wildcat cartridges, is loading for a bolt action (so only will be using a neck sizer), or someone who wants to upgrade to a nicer seater die then what they have.

Will come with the Hornady plastic case, the instructions, and the brand new seating die. MSRP is $23.79. Midway sells them for $20.49. 
I'm asking $15. In no hurry to sell, just figured I'd post it since I don't need it.

Factory New

DESCRIPTION:
01LSTAC ULTRA WITH ULTRA FEATURES
The gas operated semi-auto action is lightning fast !.  Unlike most semi-auto shotguns, the Linberta 01LSTAC ULTRA shoots all regular and higher loads without changing any parts on the gun.
The Linberta 01LSTAC ULTRA comes standard with many features normally only found on more expensive semi auto shotguns, including:
•	Trigger guard made of T7075 Aluminum and anodized.
•	Receiver made of T7075 Aluminum and anodized & special tactical pattern applied.
•	Barrels made of 4140 grade steel, drilled from solid block, honed, interior white, exterior black chrome lined.
•	Fixed Tactical Heat Shield on barrel.
Tactical Superior Handle on receiver with tactical sight Interior parts are specially heat treated using the same process used on top quality car parts for German cars.
Thicker internal parts and a single piece rock solid action bar for longer life.

FEATURES:
•	5+1 capacity, 4+1 using 3" 
•	Interchangeable choke system (Beretta/Benelli Mobile compatible chokes), comes with Muzzle Brake and Cylinder Hard Chrome Choke.
•	2 additional shims for stock adjustment
•	Sling Studs
•	Recoil Pad
•	Synthetic Stock With Vertical Pistol Grip
•	No plastic O-ring used. All metal and rock solid interior parts.

REVIEWS:
Average Rating: 4.8 of 5 Stars!  The last 10 reviews are below. 

Reviewed By: Jonathan M on 05/03/2014
Rating:  [5 of 5 Stars!] 
First opened the box it was a sight to behold much nicer than pictures show. M16 style is very well incorporated into this 12 gauge and with the integrated butt pad very little recoil. Hip firing is quite enjoyable an accurate, shot leaves the barrel as fast as you can pull the trigger. Yet to have a single shell that won't feed. Overall great quality appearance accuracy an overall value.

Reviewed By: Randall (Randy) G on 08/06/2013
Rating:  [5 of 5 Stars!]
This has quickly become my favorite shotgun. It has fired over 150 rounds and has performed flawlessly. Dis assembly for cleaning is easy and simple. Reviewed By: Ken O on 07/20/2013

Reviewed By: Ernest P on 04/01/2013
Rating:  [5 of 5 Stars!]
Got this gun and loaded it up, found some types of 2 3/4" ammo (Winchester) will only fit 4 in the tube while others (federal) will allow the advertised 5 to fit. Probably not Linberta's fault. Ran the rest of the box of 25 2 3/4 dram without any issues, then 5 rounds of 00 buckshot, no issues, rapid fire as fast as I could.
